    ns1:numberOfCredits 6.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """Innovative Teaching Methodologies Applied in the Course

Several innovative teaching methodologies (https://innovacioneducativa.upm.es/guias-pdi) are implemented in the course to motivate students and strengthen their learning:

Learning by Doing: Most classes begin with a concise introduction to the theory, which students then assimilate through a variety of exercises, problems, or case studies that let them experiment with the new concepts.
Research-Based Learning: Topics 1, 2, and 3?introductory units on the technology to be used?are consolidated through an individual research assignment for each student. Each student explores a different real-world application of agents and shares their findings in a session of oral presentations and discussion.
Collaborative Learning: The core of the course is a real?world project in which all students, working in teams, build a genuine software system under guidelines set by the instructors. Every team takes part in collaborative design sessions for each development iteration (user-story workshops), pair-based software integration meetings, and collaborative performance evaluations with continuous-improvement proposals (retrospectives). In addition, a jigsaw-style collaborative activity in Topic 2 examines the risks of agent-based software development.
Project-Based Learning: The group project is based on a need specified by the instructors, and teams develop it to build an agent-based software system. The project puts much of the master?s content into practice?agile methodologies, estimation, planning, design, programming, quality evaluation, continuous improvement, negotiation, software integration, configuration management?following the Scrum framework rigorously.
Gamification: The project?s setting is a competitive game: teams must collaborate so the overall system works, yet each team pursues its own strategy to outperform the others. At the end of the course, teams present their strategies and compete in several selected scenarios. The best-performing teams receive a bonus in their final grade."""@es ;
